    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Oregon, the F.B.I. And Our Rights</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Letter from Greg Houle, on FBI visits to men of Middle Eastern origin, says such unwarranted suspicion of innocent people causes kind of anxiety that should not happen in land of the free</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''F.B.I. Visits Provoke Waves of Worry in Middle Eastern Men'' (news article, Nov. 16): In these difficult times, it is important for Americans to remember what truly makes the United States a unique and great country: the freedoms guaranteed to all of us and protected by our Constitution.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''F.B.I. Visits Provoke Waves of Worry in Middle Eastern Men'' (news article, Nov. 16): In these difficult times, it is important for Americans to remember what truly makes the United States a unique and great country: the freedoms guaranteed to all of us and protected by our Constitution.</p>
        <p>We must be mindful not to tread on the rights of the millions of innocent Muslim Americans and Muslim nationals living in this country. Freedom is the most important thing we have, and we can't allow terrorists to take it away. Unwarranted suspicion of innocent people rightly causes anxiety. Such anxiety shouldn't happen in the land of the free.</p>
        <p>GREG HOULE  Westminster, Colo., Nov. 16, 2001</p>
      </block>
